title: Andrew Tate travel restrictions eased - but he still can't get back his cars and watches
description: Andrew Tate can travel anywhere in Romania after a court eased travel restrictions on the controversial influencer.

title: Missile that hit Poland and killed two 'was fired by Ukraine'
description: A missile strike that killed two people at a grain facility in Poland was fired by Ukraine, a Polish newspaper confirmed.

title: Three UEFA bosses opposed U-turn on Russian ban
description: The decision to reinstate Russian teams to some European competitions faced opposition from three of the five UEFA vice presidents in a private meeting of the ruling executive committee, Sky News has learned.

title: Multiple people killed in Rotterdam after two shootings
description: Multiple people have been killed in the Dutch port city of Rotterdam after two shootings at a university hospital and a home, police confirmed.

title: Student arrested after three killed in Rotterdam shootings
description: Three people have been killed in the Dutch port city of Rotterdam after two shootings at a university hospital and a home, police confirmed.

title: US soldier who fled to North Korea returns home but could face repercussions
description: The US soldier who illegally crossed the heavily armed border into North Korea from South Korea has returned home.

title: Airline vows female passengers won't be forced to have invasive examinations again
description: Qatar Airways has vowed not to repeat an "extreme incident" in which a number of Australian women were subjected to gynaecological examinations.

title: Kremlin releases video of Putin with ally after rumours of ill health
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin has met with Ramzan Kadyrov - after rumours about the Chechen leader's health.

title: Billionaire to sell 25,000 bottles of wine worth $50m
description: A wine collection dubbed the most valuable ever sold - worth an estimated $50m (£41m) - will soon be up for grabs at auction.

title: Astronaut who accidentally spent longest time in space finally returns to Earth
description: NASA astronaut Frank Rubio has returned to Earth after inadvertently breaking the record for the longest amount of time spent in space by an American.

title: Three killed in shootings and explosion linked to gang violence
description: Three people have died in less than 24 hours in separate incidents in Sweden as gang violence in the country escalates.

title: Teachers and students stabbed by teenager at Spanish school
description: A teenager has stabbed three teachers and at least one student at a school in southern Spain, police have said.

title: Switzerland has lost 10% of its glaciers in just two years in 'catastrophic' ice melt
description: Switzerland has lost 10% of its glaciers in just two years, research shows, after high summer heat and low winter snowfall.

title: Latest setback for world's most indebted property developer as chairman reported taken by police
description: Share trading in the Chinese property giant Evergrande has been suspended following reports the company founder and chairman had been taken by police.

title: Homes and roads damaged by flooding in Greece just weeks after deadly storms battered the country
description: Home and roads have been damaged by fresh floods in Greece just weeks after the country was battered by deadly storms.

title: Sky News wins International Emmy Award for coverage of Ukraine war
description: Sky News has won an International Emmy Award for its coverage of the Ukraine war.
